section.def:
franchise
                (專營權) means the right to operate a public bus
            service granted under section 5;

grantee
                (專營公司) means a company to which a franchise has
            been granted;

paragraph.content:
operates, or manages or assists in the management of, a public bus
                    service;
                    or

the scale of fares which may be charged for the carriage of passengers,
                    baggage and goods on any specified route or group of specified routes;
                    and

on any day at a frequency greater than that specified in a direction under
                        section 16(1)(a) or in an application approved under section
                        16A;

the number of passengers carried by each such bus on each day on each such route;
                    (Amended 75 of 1982 s.
                            114)

the maintenance of vehicles and stores;
                    (Amended 44 of 1984 s.
                            14)

subparagraph.content:
any vehicle used by a grantee in
                        connexion
                        with its franchise;

either in respect of the same route or any other route (where the
                        financial penalty being imposed relates to a failure as regards a route);
                        or

paragraph.content:
the grantee does not show cause why its right to operate a public bus
                    service on the specified routes set out therein should not be revoked;
                    or

where the notice was served and published prior to the revocation of the
                    franchise or the expiry of the franchise period, as from such revocation or
                    expiry;

which is subject to terms and conditions similar to the provisions applying
                    by virtue of section 25A in respect of possession of the property
                    under this section;

the total operating costs incurred by a grantee in
                    connexion
                    with its franchise;

depreciation effected in accordance with section 30;
                    (Added 30 of 1986 s.
                            2)

the gross value, as determined by the Financial Secretary, of any fixed
                    assets, services or facilities received by a grantee in lieu of any part of such
                    total gross sums;

the operating costs of the grantee;
                    (Replaced 30 of 1986 s.
                            3)

controlling or prohibiting the carriage of animals and birds on such buses;
                    (Added 44 of 1984 s.
                            19)

the control and disposal of property lost on such buses;
                    (Added 44 of 1984 s.
                            19)

regulating the number of the seated passengers and standing passengers
                    respectively whom a bus used by a grantee is constructed or adapted and fit to
                    carry;

the marks to be carried on such a bus showing the numbers referred to in
                    paragraphs (g) and (h) and the manner in which those marks are to be
                    carried;

paragraph.continued:
in any period specified in the regulations;
                    (Amended 44 of 1984 s.
                            19)

paragraph.content:
a bus route development programme, together with details of proposed changes to
                the routes operated, their frequency and vehicle allocation, on a monthly basis for
                the first 2 years of the programme and half yearly thereafter;

an estimate of the number and types of buses required in daily service to meet
                the requirements of the route development programme referred to in paragraph
                (a);

a forecast of the financial implications of the adherence to the overall
                programme prepared under section 12A, including estimates of the timing
                and magnitude of any adjustments to fare levels that may be necessary;
